* 1975: ''Island of Love Songs: Goodbye! My Love'' ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+5C9B><U+56FD><U+4E4B><U+60C5><U+6B4C>: <U+518D><U+89C1>! <U+6211><U+7684><U+7231><U+4EBA>}} ''daoguo zhi qingge: zaijian! wode airen'')
*: Also known as ''Island of Love Songs 1: Goodbye! My Love'' ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+5C9B><U+56FD><U+4E4B><U+60C5><U+6B4C><U+7B2C><U+4E00><U+96C6>: <U+518D><U+89C1>! <U+6211><U+7684><U+7231><U+4EBA>}} ''daoguo zhi qingge diyi ji: zaijian! wode airen'')
*: Mandarin rendition of the Japanese album ''K<U+016B>k<U+014D>'' / ''yukigesh<U+014D>'' ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+7A7A><U+6E2F> / <U+96EA><U+5316><U+7CA7>}})
*: In Taiwan, released by Hai Shan Records ({{lang|zh|<U+6D77><U+5C71><U+5531><U+7247>}})
* 1976: ''Island of Love Songs 2: Thinking about You Tonight / Tears of Drizzle'' ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+5C9B><U+56FD><U+4E4B><U+60C5><U+6B4C><U+7B2C><U+4E8C><U+96C6>: <U+4ECA><U+591C><U+60F3><U+8D77><U+4F60> / <U+6DDA><U+7684><U+5C0F><U+96E8>}} ''daoguo zhi qingge dier ji: jinye xiangqi ni / leide xiaoyu'')
*: Mandarin rendition of the album ''Yoru no j<U+014D>kyaku'' / ''onna no ikigai'' ({{lang|ja|<U+591C><U+306E><U+4E57><U+5BA2> / <U+5973><U+306E><U+751F><U+304D><U+304C><U+3044>}})
* 1977: ''Greatest Hits''
*: Twelve re-recordings of songs originally from Lee Fung Records ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+4E3D><U+98CE><U+5531><U+7247>}})
* 1977: ''Island of Love Songs 3: Fine Drizzle'' ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+5C9B><U+56FD><U+4E4B><U+60C5><U+6B4C><U+7B2C><U+4E09><U+96C6><U+FF1A><U+4E1D><U+4E1D><U+5C0F><U+96E8>}} ''daoguo zhi qingge disan ji: Sisi xiaoyu'')
*: Mandarin rendition of the album ''Akashia no yume'' ({{lang|ja|<U+30A2><U+30AB><U+30B7><U+30A2><U+306E><U+5922>}}); bonus addition to the song "Yun shenqing ye shen" ({{lang|zh-hant|<U+96F2><U+6DF1><U+60C5><U+4E5F><U+6DF1>}}), originally sung by [[Liu Wen Zheng]]
* 1977: ''Greatest Hits Vol. 2''
*: Some tracks are re-recordings of songs originally from Lee Fung Records ({{lang|zh-hans|<U+4E3D><U+98CE><U+5531><U+7247>}})
* 1977: ''Island of Love Songs 4: Love in Hong Kong'' ({{lang|zh-hant|<U+5CF6><U+570B><U+4E4B><U+60C5><U+6B4C><U+7B2C><U+56DB><U+96C6>: <U+9999><U+6E2F><U+4E4B><U+6200>}} ''dao guo zhi qingge disi ji: Xianggang zhi lian'')
*: Mandarin rendition of ''furusato wa doko desu ka'' ({{lang|ja|<U+3075><U+308B><U+3055><U+3068><U+306F><U+3069><U+3053><U+3067><U+3059><U+304B>}})
*: Two following different songs replaced other two Japanese songs by Teresa Teng instead of rendering them in Mandarin:
*:* "[[The Moon Represents My Heart]]" ({{lang|zh|<U+6708><U+4EAE><U+4EE3><U+8868><U+6211><U+7684><U+5FC3>}}), originally sung by Chen Fen Lan ({{lang|zh-hant|<U+9673><U+82AC><U+862D>}})
*:* "You and Me Next to Each Other" ({{lang|zh|<U+4F60><U+6211><U+76F8><U+4F34><U+5DE6><U+53F3>}}), Mandarin rendition of "Shikuramen no kahori <nowiki>[</nowiki>[[:ja:<U+30B7><U+30AF><U+30E9><U+30E1><U+30F3><U+306E><U+304B><U+307B><U+308A>|<U+30B7><U+30AF><U+30E9><U+30E1><U+30F3><U+306E><U+304B><U+307B><U+308A>]]", originally sung by [[Akira Fuse]]
